defaultWe also manage one of the largest conservation estates in the UK, covering c.143, 000 hectares. Around sixty of our reserves are farmed, co
defaultvering more than 20,000 hectares, with around 170 tenant farmers, and 200 employees. We protect and enhance habitats such as lowland farmland, heather moorland, lowland heath, wet grassland, estuaries and reed beds, and our reserves help to protect 63 of t
defaulthe 77 most rare or threatened breeding birds in the UK. 
